{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"1c0f9f0003b473430028902ea7e5776f39e96a30fb590557cb838f06cd4a075b","slug":"book.use-of-this-book","location":"/book/04_use_of_this_book.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"How to use this book (... if you ask us)","content_includes_title":false,"github":"https://github.com/florian-huber/data_science_course","copyright":"2025","numbering":{"title":{"offset":1}},"source_url":"https://github.com/florian-huber/data_science_course/blob/main/book/04_use_of_this_book.md","edit_url":"https://github.com/florian-huber/data_science_course/edit/main/book/04_use_of_this_book.md","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"04_use_of_this_book.md","url":"/data_science_course/build/04_use_of_this_book-3da80263cc3c079f892539aeaa4f4a95.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This textbook has been written to support your journey into data science as clearly and practically as possible. But like any book, its value depends on how you use it. The following suggestions will help you get the most out of it.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"dvVTrTKPQ2"}],"key":"uvDiudFCcd"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Progress at Your Own Speed","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"ekETFFc8K0"}],"key":"Bfv1cpXKbN"},{"type":"text","value":":\nData science is a broad field, and different topics will feel easier or harder depending on your background. If a concept seems difficult at first, take your time. Pause, revisit the section, and look for additional explanations elsewhere. The internet offers many excellent tutorials, videos, courses, and discussion forums on almost every topic covered in this book. The key is patience and persistence.","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"a8MitNNPCs"}],"key":"Rd2Cu7wBbs"}],"key":"pgiwETPQfN"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Learning by Doing","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"onXJXpdmv6"}],"key":"fbxQIXdFXh"},{"type":"text","value":":\nSimply reading about data science will not make you a data scientist. To really learn, you need to write code, run analyses, and work with data yourself.\nOne of the most common mistakes students make is passive learning: reading through code, following an explanation, and thinking, ","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"YHArVR8FTj"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“yeah, I got it”","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"cePMpY82YE"}],"key":"UPYq8ei53p"},{"type":"text","value":". But understanding an explanation is very different from being able to solve a problem on your own!","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"dGERCBmg4K"},{"type":"break","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"haxDORf5LU"},{"type":"text","value":"The real test of learning begins when you can apply a method independently: starting from scratch, making decisions yourself, and solving the small problems that inevitably come up along the way. For that reason, I strongly encourage you not just to read the examples in this book, but to run them, modify them, break them, and rebuild them.","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"jPVSzmBwc4"}],"key":"V06jGMfIEQ"}],"key":"xtwvyJNxAi"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Use technology as support, not as a substitute","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"aLBok0PXCo"}],"key":"iDzZdzKKgu"},{"type":"text","value":":\nWhile chatbots can serve as helpful data science assistants, they are not a substitute for your active learning. We firmly believe that the path to becoming a competent data scientist involves learning how to solve challenges on your own. Relying on a chatbot for answers is akin to copying solutions from another student or a forum. While this approach may help you complete your exercises in the short run, it won’t contribute much to your long-term learning and skill development.","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":11,"column":1}},"key":"btIkSl4kLz"}],"key":"XDqgEIFJv7"}],"key":"VS7dLaiKRa"}],"key":"PzVN8Q7JJd"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Code is the easy part","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"ACxIrjC5HZ"}],"identifier":"code-is-the-easy-part","label":"Code is the easy part","html_id":"code-is-the-easy-part","implicit":true,"key":"vXeRzpmg9u"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The next paragraphs will be on code and programming. And for many students, in particular students without a strong computer science background, the coding parts often seems to be the main challenge in the beginning. So, just as a small warning before we talk Python: A very good data scientist for sure knows how to work with code. But that would not nearly be enough. You will later see, that many data science techniques, including very fancy ones, can often we executed with just a few lines of code. The real skill therefore will not be to be able to run all available techniques on any dataset you’ll get. It is the ability to know ","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"mCLSBVfLJN"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"how to use","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"nDbWuwf19n"}],"key":"aLcAq9qAJn"},{"type":"text","value":" those methods, but also to know ","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"am6cr2ndWQ"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"when to use","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"xKtj63SLHJ"}],"key":"Ct4Y3pxHJr"},{"type":"text","value":" them! When you analyze data it will often come down to ","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"JggTQhbbit"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"asking the right questions, and knowing which tools can help you answer them","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"u8KeYnAuf9"}],"key":"L48PBYnQNu"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"x8qOPZabem"}],"key":"vClNWLSghD"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"But we will come to this many times again. For now, let’s get started with the very technical parts.","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"FhSdTTQ81I"}],"key":"TI6HYf9ftn"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Skills you should already have before you start","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"key":"zFIrZiQPxl"}],"identifier":"skills-you-should-already-have-before-you-start","label":"Skills you should already have before you start","html_id":"skills-you-should-already-have-before-you-start","implicit":true,"key":"I71w27dlgY"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This book is intended to be accessible, but it does assume some basic prior knowledge.","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"key":"gbn48YJX9Q"}],"key":"v0J3XXkjUM"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":27,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Python programming basics","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"UVT6IptCPl"}],"key":"zCNb6LurVT"},{"type":"text","value":": You should be familiar with variables, basic data types, loops, functions, and importing modules. If you are new to Python or want a refresher, good starting points include ","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"Wt8S9gvMRc"},{"type":"link","url":"https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/index.html","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Python.org’s Beginner’s Guide","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"d0pdkTA4in"}],"urlSource":"https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/index.html","key":"xn1ELvDWLq"},{"type":"text","value":", ","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"arj5Hgr8EE"},{"type":"link","url":"https://realpython.com/","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"RealPython","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"qDVAKqYqH0"}],"urlSource":"https://realpython.com/","key":"XV870zl0ZO"},{"type":"text","value":", or ","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"oNcMgXO3qX"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python-programming-language/","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GeeksforGeeks Python Programming Language","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"EBvkFs7cdf"}],"urlSource":"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python-programming-language/","key":"a4pCK16j4Y"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"NmsJNkc8j1"}],"key":"kdJx6LWK2O"}],"key":"Mknun30aYN"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":27,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Basic school-level mathematics","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"gJgF2mnMXe"}],"key":"OlRxmDIhAv"},{"type":"text","value":": A general understanding of algebra and basic statistics will be helpful, especially when it comes to understanding methods and their limitations.","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"Zt4aT8tTEk"}],"key":"X3j1sVYkxf"}],"key":"psVt2MHqIZ"}],"key":"EBJ8EXsGMi"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You do not need an advanced background in mathematics, statistics, or computer science to work with this book. But you should be willing to engage actively with both code and quantitative reasoning.","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"hSTFNb0gLK"}],"key":"RWmFzXYtRY"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why Python?","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"VEAxKkEkfR"}],"identifier":"why-python","label":"Why Python?","html_id":"why-python","implicit":true,"key":"lVPFqvJaCu"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Python, over the years, has emerged as the lingua franca of data science. But why?","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"key":"AL6p8oiMzC"}],"key":"RnLpWfNhw8"},{"type":"list","ordered":true,"start":1,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A rich ecosystem of libraries","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"key":"vKLd70bNXA"}],"key":"roxGHrQo4z"},{"type":"text","value":": Python offers powerful libraries such as NumPy, pandas, matplotlib, seaborn, and scikit-learn for numerical computing, data handling, visualization, and machine learning.","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"key":"pqJrKkVSXA"}],"key":"xPQzD6ZUPK"}],"key":"tqxFD3wjhT"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Readable syntax","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"key":"K8vwvbn8HM"}],"key":"bLlsQEBodk"},{"type":"text","value":": Python is often easier to read and write than many other programming languages, which makes it especially suitable for beginners.","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"key":"yojsfHnIoU"}],"key":"dORPGHCEXq"}],"key":"kQLOQCHih7"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Strong community support","position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"key":"tvixticGHp"}],"key":"gkAGfDsqZO"},{"type":"text","value":": Because Python is so widely used, there are countless tutorials, examples, forums, and community resources available.","position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"key":"vKEZRKIFsH"}],"key":"DoSy89aiHo"}],"key":"rBvtT7E47q"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1},"end":{"line":37,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1},"end":{"line":37,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Flexibility","position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1},"end":{"line":37,"column":1}},"key":"Kbrleyr5AY"}],"key":"xGBt5lpt4O"},{"type":"text","value":": Python can be used for many different tasks, from quick scripts and data analysis to machine learning and web development.","position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1},"end":{"line":37,"column":1}},"key":"XWrxsdpyK1"}],"key":"RdWA5nwIC6"}],"key":"RGNWgNrMhh"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Wide adoption in academia and industry","position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"key":"XnKbErBKKN"}],"key":"bTB9nIC2O2"},{"type":"text","value":": Python is used extensively in research, education, and industry, making it a practical language to learn.","position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"key":"kInYJTWdi8"}],"key":"lQEG5koYyG"}],"key":"itxZDD5Kca"}],"key":"yxXkaZgstL"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Other languages and tools, such as R, Julia, or KNIME, also have important strengths. But Python’s combination of accessibility, flexibility, and ecosystem makes it an excellent choice for this book. All code examples in the book are therefore written in Python.","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"key":"VsO9wwR1LN"}],"key":"JBMisHtHNH"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Open source libraries","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"key":"PDWiWvOIXo"}],"identifier":"open-source-libraries","label":"Open source libraries","html_id":"open-source-libraries","implicit":true,"key":"viAWL0EqZs"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Python’s prowess in data science can be attributed to its incredible libraries. These libraries, backed by a robust open-source community, are the backbone of various data operations:","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"key":"lL7rhWK4xB"}],"key":"CZjgollSYe"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":52,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"NumPy","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"key":"dg0fErol8z"}],"key":"hbtmJjkVhx"},{"type":"text","value":": Fundamental package for numerical computations in Python. ","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"key":"rkO6sUSATX"},{"type":"link","url":"https://numpy.org/doc/","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"NumPy Documentation","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"key":"sIlkw8Di1z"}],"urlSource":"https://numpy.org/doc/","key":"IH6NvlHUGf"}],"key":"TtBE02ehyF"}],"key":"YVnpkRNBnl"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"pandas","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"key":"avMhBBZ8Bs"}],"key":"rE3aXt18nz"},{"type":"text","value":": Offers data structures and operations for manipulating numerical tables and time series. ",